<subSubSection id="27AC49FED1D60D60BD3363B7F907562B" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="59F61ABDAD3FB160A56F55C176FC8421" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2AAA6CAB77AFDB9B132D969899E5D4F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
<taxonomicName id="366CDBD385C537728BD5675610DABA8F" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Encyrtus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Encyrtus rhodococcusiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodococcusiae">
<emphasis id="EB341B6869AE94332519B98134FDD2D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Encyrtus rhodococcusiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed morphologically within the 
<taxonomicName id="DC1B150B2771C3CF69EC94FB2A66F4F7" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="D9D683BF3052D0E92FB13D9BF51AE5AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex through the combination of the 2nd outer plate less than 0.6
<normalizedToken id="D7EB723EEE97BEDEDCF0252A44EA7537" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the ovipositor shield (2nd outer plate at least 0.65
<normalizedToken id="4902D9766EE18F48DFEA8EB360E464EF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the ovipositor shield in 
<taxonomicName id="E4CB7C81064E542A521A933FFA20236F" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. eulecaniumiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eulecaniumiae">
<emphasis id="94D3D19E116B1C162D7A5912C863D769" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. eulecaniumiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and hypopygium deeply concave (hypopygium shallowly concave in 
<taxonomicName id="10E8ACA3CB82FDD795E279D74A9652FD" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="949240CD90EB54A5CD16B8756CE6601C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="F6EE5843FFE924AEE88118FAA08CEE1F" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Encyrtus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Encyrtus rhodococcusiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodococcusiae">
<emphasis id="6204010CE2238F52D591D0424D873032" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Encyrtus rhodococcusiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be further differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="A61A7C5EBB19CAE03ABB3DD19823F042" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="9D18609C0084ED45E1F4E61424E956B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the ventral surface of the clava more than 1.5
<normalizedToken id="B8FD7AE47DD6F8603E64912923D5BE2E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the dorsal one (in 
<taxonomicName id="8A1A3EE5FB60D5D4E7B073DA7AF65E3C" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="242803CA5161C7AE4DD7F6CEB9464C78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ventral surface of the clava is always less than 1.5
<normalizedToken id="E82831DEC40DAD08B56BC782D4107789" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as the dorsal one). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="DC71A9764EB0B05AD2F1F9C23158246B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D285AAE393A1FD98AD7EE5E7C0BAAB85" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. rhodococcusiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodococcusiae">
<emphasis id="0FC3FA8C26CAC7FEB2ADC3588F4283C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. rhodococcusiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be molecularly distinguished from its closest allies (
<taxonomicName id="06FDA6944D66A1DFA6D66BAA83818DE5" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="8AC0F78C35226FBC15FFECBAA0027601" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FD8BFBD81A21701C30343910FE185D8B" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. eulecaniumiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eulecaniumiae">
<emphasis id="DC44517402F10B2E62C1A1073E145AD3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. eulecaniumiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by having the following nucleotides in the COI marker: 14 (T), 26 (A), 102 (A), 149 (A), 161 (C), 176 (G), 215 (G), 266 (T), 269 (A), 281 (T), 389 (A), 446 (A), 468 (C), 470 (T) 521 (T) and 530 (G). 
<taxonomicName id="656F3D09A9AEA739540FA88D31577989" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Encyrtus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Encyrtus rhodococcusiae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodococcusiae">
<emphasis id="5ABD89F14D86610F31B437453A5CF583" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Encyrtus rhodococcusiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also unique within the 
<taxonomicName id="2B286462D85775581670C426A9EE45DF" class="Insecta" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. sasakii" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasakii">
<emphasis id="7A874896D7F04E93A50C5EE6D8E3F81F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">E. sasakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in attacking the coccid species 
<taxonomicName id="266950087B113BE9D00438138EC4573C" authorityName="Borchsenius" authorityYear="1955" class="Chlorophyceae" family="Palmellaceae" genus="Rhodococcus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhodococcus sariuoni" order="Tetrasporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="sariuoni">
<emphasis id="B79BC7A739094A3EFB464F2F3CFC99F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Rhodococcus sariuoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Borchsenius.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40446DE5D2705BBEF2F7F3A58E63F325" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph id="A90D0B1A74C6E8C47A2CE26F885C03B4" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D86F38B4E4EB7390CB829A41B6479F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">
(reproduced from 
<bibRefCitation id="FE1C83F7B1BBC981993F0569AA3EF0DA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
) Female - Length including ovipositor 1.9 mm. 
<emphasis id="E0D01556708F08C67F9F957657639CF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Colouration</emphasis>
: Head black around ocellar area, frontovertex black; malar space brown; antenna with scape yellowish brown; pedicel and flagellum dark brown; maxillary and labial palpi yellowish brown; pronotum dark brown to black dorsally, laterally pale brown; thorax covered with dark-brown setae; mesoscutum mostly black dorsally, laterally brown; sctuellum black with a broad transverse yellow band and a tuft of black bristles apically; metanotum dark brown; tegula dark brown; mesopleuron pale brown; fore and hind coxae brownish yellow (
<bibRefCitation id="6F0163B39492E4466C137FE20136D87E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7d, f); mid coxa mostly brown (
<bibRefCitation id="BB52CBABEA0893F856F53A4E507CE931" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7e); legs otherwise dark brown; basal one third of forewing hyaline, infuscate elsewhere; forewing with a series of long bristles just below the apical third of submarginal; propodeum brown dorsally, yellowish brown laterally; gaster black; ovipositor sheaths yellow, except apex one-third dark brown (
<bibRefCitation id="30B61CE9DC29EEE7DB651269B0AA5BE5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7b). 
<emphasis id="B03F7F10139DB6E64F7A81E29BF31760" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Head</emphasis>
: frontovertex about half the head width; ocelli forming an obtuse angle (~120°); scrobes quite shallow and ∩-shaped in frontal view; eye at least superficially bare; torulus separated from mouth margin by about one of its own length; toruli separated from each other by about 2.5
<normalizedToken id="9BCD48C7FE9EDAE8B01DCE4C4C897C40" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their own diameter; antenna with scape subcylindrical, 3.4
<normalizedToken id="0056016C9A7874574DCD33A04829CD3D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; pedicel subtriangular, 1.4
<normalizedToken id="ABB67398374B4E2B99BF307DA608CED7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad and as broad as scape. Antenna (
<bibRefCitation id="6F404DFBBD05146708BCF5453F3174A7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7a) 13-segmented, scape cylindrical; clava 3-segmented, its apex distinctly truncate; mandible plow shaped; clypeus with three to six conspicuous, long, suberect setae; maxillary and labial palpi with 4 and 3 segments respectively. 
<emphasis id="9BC4E1425BC0BE9D0002F0691C1240A2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Thorax</emphasis>
: Mesoscutum 1.44
<normalizedToken id="68F39CF651564C827AB06D225811561B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
wider than long, uniformly convex, setose and finely reticulated, without notauli. Pronotum very short, about one eleventh the mesoscutum length, with polygonal reticulation; scutellum about 1.2
<normalizedToken id="620C147D379E62E9D061DD57B794E592" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, sculpture anteriorly similar to that of mesoscutum; forewing (
<bibRefCitation id="D98CEA61938CF53B980B6650FA308802" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" author="Wang, Y" journalOrPublisher="Scientific Reports" pageId="0" pageNumber="129" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B72" refString="Wang, Y, Zhou, QS, Qiao, HJ, Zhang, AB, Yu, F, Wang, XB, Zhu, CD, Zhang, YZ, 2016. Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Scientific Reports 6: 1 - 16, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" title="Formal nomenclature and description of cryptic species of the Encyrtus sasakii complex (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1038/srep34372" volume="6" year="2016">Wang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7c) about 2.3
<normalizedToken id="F1B71307E2419D6DEDC3B4D60DBECEBA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; costal cell with more than one line of setae dorsally; stigma vein apically curved. 
<emphasis id="FDFC740061A0026AA2552DA529DE739E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Gaster</emphasis>
: Hypopygium almost reaching apex of gaster.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
